1.2 Commercial Use
The use of any part of the CobbleHammers Software—including but not limited to code, assets, textures, models, or derivatives thereof—for any commercial purpose is strictly prohibited.
This includes, without limitation:

Selling or licensing the Software or its components;
Using the Software or its components in paid mods, paid access content, or premium features;
Locking any content derived from the Software behind paywalls, donation rewards, server crate keys, or other monetized systems.
Commercial use is defined as any activity that results in direct or indirect financial gain, whether monetary or in-kind (e.g., donations, subscriptions, ad revenue, or exclusive access).
Any exception must be explicitly authorized in writing by DAN2026.

1.2.1 Modpack Usage
CobbleHammers may be freely included in any modpack — public or private — without requiring permission, provided:

The modpack does not lock CobbleHammers or its features behind a paywall or paid tier;
Clear credit is given to DAN2026 as the original author;
No part of CobbleHammers is repackaged or redistributed as a standalone paid product.

1.3 Modification & Redistribution
You are permitted to create and distribute sidemods — that is, separate modules, extensions, or addons that interact with CobbleHammers but do not contain substantial portions of its original code — without requesting permission, provided they do not include, copy, or heavily derive from CobbleHammers source files.

If your modification includes significant sections of code, logic, or structure from CobbleHammers, you must:

Give clear credit to DAN2026 as the original author;
Include an intact copy of this license file;
Not use the modification for any commercial purpose.

Redistribution of any portion of the original CobbleHammers Software, whether modified or unmodified, on public platforms (e.g., Modrinth, CurseForge) must include:

Clear credit to the original author(s), and
An intact copy of this license file.

